The paper deals with medical image analysis, specifically segmentation of lesion regions in skin images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed method involves the use of a fully convolutional network with new dense pooling layers, which is a machine learning approach (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning techniques, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The authors also discuss related work on skin lesion segmentation using image retrieval (cs.IR) and texture analysis (cs.MM), indicating that these sub-categories are also relevant to the paper.
